1 o'clock in the morning hungry and tired. Listen to the rustle of the leaves under foot. A rabbit or mouse crosses my path. The smell of summer flowers sleeping in the night. Just walking down a lonely lane with the moon to light my way. Carrying but a bag full of nothing.
In my pockets just bits and pieces, amongst it 10p. Thinking about being rich and famous something I may never be. I hear a noise,something quiet but it must have been a mouse. The sweep of an owl flies overhead. I see the far off lights of the town shine in the night.
{Sandra Welsh}
